description.narrative: UNICEF support to the Iraqi Federal Ministry of Education has resulted in the development of the final draft of the Iraq National Education Strategy (INES) 2022-2031. This document is a part of a government-wide effort to improve the quality and efficiency of the national and sub-national education system. UNICEF’s advocacy and technical support also resulted in the finalization and approval of the Early Childhood Development strategy and the Refugee Integration Policy; these two key policy documents will positively impact the sustainable access to quality education for young and refugee children. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/01/2022
